      <!-- Integrity mechanisms -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Integrity</div>
          <h2>How the schema defends correctness.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Unique idempotency</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>merchant_checkout_sessions.idempotency_key</code> has a partial UNIQUE index. Two
              concurrent creates with the same key collide at the database — there is no "last write wins"
              path that could double-pay a customer (migration 031).
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Row locks at claim time</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              Checkout claim uses <code>SELECT … FOR UPDATE NOWAIT</code> — if another worker already holds
              the lock, the caller fails fast rather than waits, and the client retries. Prevents two
              settlement workers from racing the same session.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Enum types for state machines</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>approval_status</code>, <code>approval_urgency</code>, CHECK constraints on
              <code>kya_status</code>, <code>settlement_type</code>. Invalid states become database errors,
              not runtime surprises.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Cascading deletes where ownership is clear</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>ba_session.user_id → ba_user(id) ON DELETE CASCADE</code>;
              <code>mandate_state_transitions.mandate_id → spending_mandates(id) ON DELETE CASCADE</code>.
              Ownership deletions don't leave orphans.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Reconciliation queue survives restarts</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              If a ledger append fails after on-chain execution, the reconciliation entry lands in
              <code>reconciliation_queue</code> with <code>status='pending'</code> — not in RAM. A worker
              drains it on the next process boot (migration 057).
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Policy evidence is cryptographically hashed</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>policy_versions.hash</code> and <code>policy_decisions.evidence_hash</code> mean a
              policy decision can be proven-in-court without trusting the Sardis log pipeline. Migration 040
              and 041.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

